  <title>Environment Variables</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>EMULATR_AUTOSNAP</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_CONSOLE_PORT</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_CONSOLE_SNAPSHOT</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_FLASH_ROM</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_MEMDIAG</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_NO_AUTOLOAD</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_NO_PUTTY</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_PLATFORM_CONFIG</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_STOP_FILE</keyword>
    <keyword>environment variables</keyword>
    <keyword>getenv</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header><para styleclass="Heading1">Environment Variables</para></header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The runtime environment variables EmulatR reads at launch, plus the compile-time flags that look like env vars but are CMake options. All values are read with <text styleclass="Code Example">std::getenv</text> -- set them in the launching shell before starting the process (inline bash assignment is the normal form).</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Three gotchas</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">- <text style="font-weight:bold;">Presence, not value.</text> Most gates test only that the variable is set, so <text styleclass="Code Example">VAR=0</text> still ENABLES them. Exceptions that parse a value are noted below.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">- <text style="font-weight:bold;">Read once.</text> The trace / diagnostic gates cache their result on first call; exporting them mid-run has no effect.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">- <text style="font-weight:bold;">Paths are CWD-relative.</text> The stop sentinel and the snapshots directory resolve against the launch directory; launch from the Emulatr root.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Snapshot / autoload</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="6" colcount="3" style="border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#000000; border-style:solid; head-row-background-color:#00ffff; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <thead style="vertical-align:top">
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Variable</text></para></td>
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Default</text></para></td>
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Effect</text></para></td>
      </thead>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_CONSOLE_SNAPSHOT</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">off</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Arms the console-marker snapshot watch; a matching input line writes a .axpsnap.</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_SNAPSHOT_MARKER</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">set oem_string snapshot</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">The exact line that triggers a console snapshot (internal whitespace NOT normalized).</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_AUTOSNAP</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">on</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">=off</text> disables periodic auto saves. Mirrors <text styleclass="Code Example">--autosnapshot off</text>.</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_NO_AUTOLOAD</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">unset</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Skip autoload-newest; force a genuine cold boot. Mirrors <text styleclass="Code Example">--no-autoload</text>.</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_SNAPSHOT_PRUNE</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">unset</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Enable pruning of old snapshots (off by default).</para></td></tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Process / platform</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="6" colcount="3" style="border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#000000; border-style:solid; head-row-background-color:#00ffff; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <thead style="vertical-align:top">
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Variable</text></para></td>
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Default</text></para></td>
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Effect</text></para></td>
      </thead>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_STOP_FILE</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">EMULATR_STOP</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Path of the graceful-stop sentinel; touch it to flush flash NVRAM and exit cleanly.</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_NO_PUTTY</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">unset</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Do not auto-launch PuTTY; the listen socket still comes up.</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_CONSOLE_PORT</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">10023</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">TCP console port (PuTTY auto-launch follows it). Give each instance its own port.</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_FLASH_ROM</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">ds10_flash.rom</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Backing file for the flash / NVRAM image. Isolate it per instance to avoid corruption.</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_PLATFORM_CONFIG</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">derived DS10</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Override the platform manifest.</para></td></tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Logging / diagnostics and device traces</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="7" colcount="2" style="border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#000000; border-style:solid; head-row-background-color:#00ffff; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <thead style="vertical-align:top">
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Variable</text></para></td>
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Effect</text></para></td>
      </thead>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_CHIPSET_DIAG_OFF</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Silences the chipset CSR diagnostics (inverted sense: setting it turns them OFF).</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_TRACE_WINDOW</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Forces the retire-compact trace window.</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_RETIRE_TRACE_DIR</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Output directory for retire / breakpoint / profiler trace files.</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_IIC_TRACE</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Trace PCF8584 IIC bus transactions.</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_FLASH_TRACE</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Trace FlashRom command / erase / write activity.</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_PIC_TRACE</text></para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Trace the 8259 PIC pair (IRQ assert / EOI).</para></td></tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Probe / experimental</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_IDLEWARP</text> fast-forwards the idle loop to the next timer tick (clean). <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_GCT_WATCH</text>, <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_BREAK_ON_PA10</text>, <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_CHECKPOINTS</text>, and <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_GATE</text> are pinpoint debug gates. Note: <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_RSCCWARP</text> is QUARANTINED (caused boot corruption) and <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_TICKWARP</text> is a deprecated no-op.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Compile-time flags (NOT runtime env vars)</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">These are CMake options baked in at build time -- setting them in the shell does nothing: <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_MEMDIAG</text> (per-instruction logging, ~900x slowdown, keep OFF), <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_DIAGNOSTIC_LOGGING</text> (non-Release per-subsystem logging), and the <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_LOG_*</text> spdlog level macros.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">CLI flags that mirror env vars</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">--autosnapshot off</text> = <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_AUTOSNAP=off</text>; <text styleclass="Code Example">--no-autoload</text> = <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_NO_AUTOLOAD=1</text>. <text styleclass="Code Example">--max-cycles</text>, <text styleclass="Code Example">--snapshot-on-pc</text>, and <text styleclass="Code Example">--snapshot-name-tag</text> have no env equivalent.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
